The paper deals with the problem of recognizing moving objects in video images using artificial intelligence. Specifically, it uses the SP Theory of Intelligence, which is a framework of artificial intelligence, to detect and recognize objects of interest in video frames with multilevel hierarchical parts and subparts. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised learning and optimization algorithms, which are common in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of species-based Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO) also suggests that the paper may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with tracking moving objects, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO).
